DependentParameter

public DependentParameter(java.lang.String name,
                          ParameterConstraintAPI constraint,
                          java.lang.String units,
                          java.lang.Object value)
                   throws ConstraintException
This is the main constructor. All subclass constructors call this one. Constraints must be set first, because the value may not be an allowed one. Null values are always allowed in the constructor.
Parameters:
name - Name of this parameter
constraint - Constraints for this Parameter. May be set to null
units - The units for this parameter
value - The value object of this parameter.
Throws:
ConstraintException - Description of the Exception
ConstraintException - This is thrown if the passes in parameter is not allowed

getIndependentParametersIterator

public java.util.ListIterator getIndependentParametersIterator()
Returns an iterator of all parameters in the list.

Note: SWR - I choose to implement the iterator an easy way but not the best way. I create a vector, add all parameters from the Hashtable. Quick and dirty. May want to improve in the future.

getIndependentParametersKey

public java.lang.String getIndependentParametersKey()
Since the storage of the independent parameters are a TreeMap, the parameters are sorted by their names. This guarentees that this function always returns the same value if more than one independent parameter. A normal iterator doesn't guarentee order of returned elements in a Hashtable or HashMap
Specified by:
getIndependentParametersKey in interface DependentParameterAPI

containsIndependentParameter

public boolean containsIndependentParameter(java.lang.String paramName)
Checks if the parameter exists in the list, returns true only if it finds a name match. No other comparision is done. We may want to increase the comparision in the future, i.e. returns true if has same independent parameters, etc.
